              <file>page11/pw037.mp3</file>
              <text><![CDATA[In this photo you can see manifolds which connect deck pipelines with shore hoses or loading arms. Every manifold end has a removable blank flange. The shore loading arms or hoses are connected to the manifold flanges which have been selected for the cargo. Manifold valves are used to route the cargo to the desired pipeline.

 At the loading port the cargo is pumped on board by shore pumps. The cargo flow is controlled remotely from a pumping room which is ashore on a pumping plant. Click on NEXT to see the pumping plant.
]]></text>
